==English==

===Etymology===
From the practice of, especially, Protestants of using quotations from the Bible to support positions taken in sermons or discussions, citing the specific chapter and verse of the books of the Bible.

===Verb===
{{infl|en|verb|head=to [[cite]] [[chapter]] and [[verse]]}}

# To give specific references to an [[authoritative]] book, as the Bible or a book of [[statutes]] or regulations, to support a statement.
# {{idiom}} To speak with the authority of specific verifiable knowledge.